    "recap_headline": "Washington State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "PULLMAN, Wash. (March 21, 2026)\n\u2013\nMatt Priest\nhustled down the first base line to beat out an game-winning walkoff RBI-fielder's choice to beat Grand Canyon 6-5 in 10 innings at Bailey-Brayton Field Saturday afternoon.\nThe Cougars (9-12, 3-2 Mountain West) rallied to tie the game in three straight innings, scoring once in the eighth to tie things at three, scored once in the ninth to tie things at four and scored twice in the tenth to clinch the series from Grand Canyon (8-16, 0-2 Mountain West).\nGavin Roy\n,\nMax Hartman\n,\nMason Pirello\nand\nRyan Skjonsby\neach recorded two hits while starter\nGriffin Smith\nworked into the seventh inning and allowed just one earned run.\nKEY MOMENTS OF THE GAME\nHartman's RBI-infield single in the third inning gave WSU a 1-0 lead and both teams traded runs in the fifth before GCU took a 3-2 lead with two runs in the seventh.\nRyan Skjonsby\ntied the game in the eighth with an RBI-single through the right side but GCU retook the lead with a solo homer to lead off the ninth. WSU put runners on the corners with one out in the bottom of the ninth before\nNoah Thein\nbrought home the tying run with a safety squeeze bunt to score Roy.\nGrand Canyon took a 5-4 lead after a bases-loaded walk in the tenth but Cougars answered as Skjonsby singled back up the middle to start the inning,\nCam Macleod\nreached on a GCU infield bobble and\nKyler Northrop\nbeat out an infield bunt single to load the bases. Roy brought in Skjonsby with a sacrifice fly to right field as Macleod moved up to third on the play. Priest followed with a ground ball to second who flipped to second base to try to turn the double play but Priest beat the throw at first as the Macleod scored the game-winner.\nINSIDE THE BOX SCORE\nGavin Roy\nwalked in the 1\nst\nto extend his on-base streak to 8 games\nRoy doubled in the 3\nrd\nto extend his hitting streak to 8 games\nHartman's infield single in the 3\nrd\nextended his hitting streak to 6 games\nMatt Priest\nsingled in the 7\nth\nto extend his hitting streak to 5 games and on-base streak to 7 games\nDane Chavez\nsingled in the 9\nth\nto extend his on-base streak to 12 games\nWSU recorded its 1\nst\nwalkoff win of the season and first since beating San Jose State 6-5 last season\nRylan Haider\nworked 1.1 scoreless innings with 3 strikeouts\nScott Rienguette\nearned the win after working the final 2 innings\nON DEC\nK\nThe series wraps up Sunday at 12:05 p.m.",
